      'content-static': `# Resume Optimization Rules

## The Core Principle

The job description is the ONLY filter that matters. Every single line on the optimized resume must earn its place by directly supporting what the job posting asks for.

## Before Writing Anything

Create an explicit checklist of every requirement, responsibility, skill, tool, and qualification mentioned in the job posting. This checklist is the blueprint. Nothing goes on the resume unless it maps to something on this checklist.

## Hard Rules

- If a bullet point does not directly address a posting requirement — DELETE IT.
- Do not include skills, tools, or platforms not mentioned or clearly implied by the job description, even if Jack has them.
- Do not add technical methods, niche analytics terms, or specialized tools just to sound advanced.
- If a posting requires a skill not confirmed in the base resume or Skills Inventory, do not include it. Flag it separately.
- Entire past roles can be reduced to a single title/date line or removed entirely if they contribute nothing.
- The summary section must be rewritten from scratch for each role.
- After drafting, re-read every line: "Does the job posting ask for this?" If the answer is not a clear yes, remove it.

## ATS Understanding

- ATS systems are databases, not scoring algorithms.
- They search for exact keyword matches.
- Database retrieval comes first, then human review.
- The top one-third of page one is critical real estate.

## 2026 Hiring Manager Reality

- Spends ~7 seconds on initial review.
- Can instantly recognize AI-generated content (watch for: "delve," "tapestry," excessive flowery language).
- Looks for measurable outcomes, not task descriptions.

## DOCX Layout Requirements

- Single-column layout only. No tables, text boxes, sidebars, columns, or multi-column structures.
- ATS-safe typography: Calibri, Arial, Georgia, Aptos, Helvetica, Verdana, or Tahoma.
- Name block in the main body (not in a header/footer).
- Clear section headers.
- Standard round or square bullets only.
- 0.5 to 1 inch margins (1 inch preferred).
- 1.0 or 1.15 line spacing.
- No decorative elements: no lines, borders, shading, graphics, images, icons, or text boxes.

## Confirmed ATS Section Headings

- Professional Summary or Summary
- Work Experience or Professional Experience
- Education
- Skills
- Certifications (when relevant)`,

